-- Mexico Stocks: Ara, Cemex, Homex Advance; Liverpool Shares Drop
-- B y   J o n a t h a n   J .   L e v i n
-- 2012-01-12T22:17:53Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-12/mexico-stocks-ara-cemex-homex-advance-liverpool-shares-drop.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of the close of trading.  The IPC  index  was little changed at 37,320.97.  Most homebuilders and cement company  Cemex (CEMEXCPO)  SAB gained amid
optimism about a drop in borrowing costs at debt auctions in
 Europe .  Spain  sold 10 billion euros ($13 billion) of bonds,
twice the target for the sale, while Italy sold 12 billion euros
of bills, easing concern the countries would struggle to finance
their debts.  Desarrolladora Homex SAB (HOMEX*)  , Mexico’s largest
homebuilder, jumped 3.5 percent to 41.97 pesos. Builder
 Consorcio Ara SAB (ARA*)   gained 1 percent to 4.16 pesos.
Cemex (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the Americas,
advanced 1.8 percent to 7.73 pesos.  Mexican retailers slumped as U.S. retail sales rose less
than projected in December.  Wal-Mart de Mexico SAB  (WALMEXV MM), Latin America’s
largest retailer, fell 0.2 percent to 37.61 pesos.  Grupo Elektra
SA (ELEKTRA*)  , the retail and banking company controlled by
billionaire  Ricardo Salinas , tumbled 3.6 percent to 1,337.84
pesos.  El Puerto de Liverpool SAB  (LIVEPOLC MM), a Mexican
department store operator, declined 1.2 percent to 99.79 pesos.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Jonathan J. Levin in Mexico City at 
